The `Uncaught ReferenceError: LoginPage is not defined` error typically happens when a component is used (referenced) before it has been defined or declared in the code. Since `LoginPage` is a functional component defined within `index.tsx`, this error suggests that the `App` component (which tries to render `<LoginPage />`) is defined *before* the `LoginPage` component in the file, or `LoginPage` is missing entirely.

Looking at the previous file content, `LoginPage` *was* defined before `App`, so the issue is likely due to a copy-paste error or truncated file generation where the definition was lost or the order was messed up during the last "full file" restore.

I will fix this by ensuring `LoginPage` is defined *before* `App` in the `index.tsx` file. I will also clean up the `index.html` to remove the duplicate stylesheet link.

